<exercise checkit-seed="0001" checkit-slug="B2" checkit-title="Sampling Techniques">
  <statement>
      
      
      
      
      
      <p>
          For each of the following, classify the sampling technique described as <em>Simple Random Sample</em>, <em>Stratified Random Sampling</em>, <em>Cluster Sampling</em> or <em>Multi-Stage Sampling</em>.  Be sure to justify your choices.
          <ol>
              <li>To measure the spread of a species of bovine flea at a ranch, random cows are selected and tested for fleas.</li>
              <li>To measure the cost of living in a city, the city is divided into square mile regions, and a few of these regions are randomly selected, and all the grocery stores within them have their prices analyzed.</li>
              <li>To measure the cost of living in a city, the city is divided into square mile regions, some regions are randomly selected, and a few grocery stores within each selected region are randomly selected to have their prices analyzed.</li>
              <li>To measure the effects of a sewage malfunction in a town, city randomly choses homes to have their water tested.</li>
              <li>To measure potential allergic reactions to a medication,  users of the medication are seperated by age range, and a few age ranges are randomly selected to be tested.</li>
              <li>To measure student response to a new general education policy, the administration randomly selects students from the university to survey.</li>
          </ol>
          
      </p>
      
      
     
      
          
          
          
          
      
  </statement>
  <answer>
      <title>Partial Solution:</title>
      
      
      
      
     <p>
          <ol>
              <li>Simple Random Sampling</li>
              <li>Cluster Sampling</li>
              <li>Multi-Stage Sampling</li>
              <li>Simple Random Sampling</li>
              <li>Cluster Sampling</li>
              <li>Simple Random Sampling</li>
          </ol>
          
      </p>
          
      
  </answer>
</exercise>
